<TEXT>nityānando ’ṇusaṃghasya śaśvat{ }kalyāṇakārakaḥ || 2:14||</TEXT>
<APP> \vd <LEM>śaśvat</LEM> \emend; sasvat \msA </APP>
<TR>Śiva is without beginning and end and is omniscient and omnipotent with respect to all things, all-pervasive, controlled, consisting in eternal bliss, ever performing what is beneficial for [all] souls (\skt{aṇusaṃghasya}).</TR>
<TEXT>tam evoddiśya bhāvena saddravyāṇāṃ visarjjanam | </TEXT>
