<TEXT>sa yajñaḥ saṅgatārthan tu śivāṇvor deśikakriyā || 2:15||</TEXT>
<TR>The offering of good substances with devotion for the intention of this same [Śiva] is [what we call] “sacrifice” (\skt{yajñaḥ}), for the purpose of uniting the soul and Śiva.  It is the work of the guru.</TR>
