<TEXT>aṃgāni kumbhapūrvāṇi paśupaścimakāni ca || 2:16||</TEXT>
<TR>The materials (\skt{dravyāṇi)) for this [initiation, which have been mentioned in 2:2 above] begin with things to be scattered and include such items as chalk.  The essential constituents (\skt{aṅgāni}) [which were also mentioned in 2:2] begin with the pots [in which the mantra-deities are installed(?)] and end with the bound soul [who is to be initiated].</TR>
